WEBVTT

00:00:08.800 --> 00:00:11.280
What is this?!

00:00:16.250 --> 00:00:23.250
This is impossible.

00:00:27.031 --> 00:00:28.031
What?

00:00:28.261 --> 00:00:29.881
What is going on?
Hey!

00:00:30.361 --> 00:00:34.161
It's freezing.
Hey, I can't even move.

00:00:34.741 --> 00:00:36.581
Hey!
Is anyone there?

00:00:39.182 --> 00:00:43.042
Wait, seriously.
Where am I?

00:00:44.622 --> 00:00:47.922
What mountain is this?
Ah, there are so many bugs.

00:00:48.582 --> 00:00:50.642
I can't get out. Seriously.
I can't get out.

00:00:51.122 --> 00:00:54.322
Hey, what am I supposed to do?
If nobody comes, I'm dead.

00:01:06.743 --> 00:01:12.923
Can I take this off?

00:01:12.983 --> 00:01:19.343
Excuse me, can I take this off now?
Huh? Go ahead.

00:01:20.503 --> 00:01:21.583
Huh?
Huh?

00:01:21.723 --> 00:01:22.743
Huh?
You're taking it off? Huh?

00:01:22.843 --> 00:01:27.023
No, no.
Huh?

00:01:27.143 --> 00:01:30.383
Huh? What do you mean? You really took it
off? Wait, I can?

00:01:30.383 --> 00:01:34.624
I can take it off? Who are you? What? What
the hell is this? I can take it off?

00:01:36.024 --> 00:01:38.044
What?
You're taking it off?

00:01:38.444 --> 00:01:40.284
Fine, whatever. What? This is scary. Stop.
Say something.

00:01:40.304 --> 00:01:42.204
Stop it already. Take it off.
I am, I am.

00:01:42.264 --> 00:01:46.384
Who the hell are you? Seriously.
What is this thing?

00:01:47.784 --> 00:01:50.784
Takano?
Or rather, what is this?

00:01:52.024 --> 00:01:53.744
I don't get it.
No, this is...

00:01:53.844 --> 00:01:57.345
What is this? What is this? I seriously
don't get it. Huh, what?

00:01:59.085 --> 00:02:03.005
What is this, seriously?
There's nothing here.

00:02:04.445 --> 00:02:06.185
Huh?

00:02:14.415 --> 00:02:15.415
What is this?

00:02:18.965 --> 00:02:21.505
What?
What is this? What is this?

00:02:22.406 --> 00:02:23.406
Candy.
Huh?

00:02:26.126 --> 00:02:28.266
What?
Whoa, what is this?

00:02:30.026 --> 00:02:33.046
Candy.
What is going on?

00:02:33.406 --> 00:02:36.686
Wait, my hands are tied together.
What is this?

00:02:40.386 --> 00:02:45.546
Stop it, come on.

00:02:47.326 --> 00:02:52.307
It's all candy.
What is this?

00:02:54.107 --> 00:02:55.107
What? What is going on?

00:02:56.847 --> 00:03:03.847
What is this supposed to be?

00:03:05.197 --> 00:03:06.197
Can I take it?

00:03:12.307 --> 00:03:13.307
Ah!
Whoa, who's there?

00:03:13.547 --> 00:03:15.628
Hey, hey.
Come on, don't do that.

00:03:15.828 --> 00:03:18.548
Whoa, you scared me.
It's Shinichi.

00:03:19.928 --> 00:03:24.948
What is this?
Whoa, what is this? Creepy.

00:03:25.148 --> 00:03:28.408
Creepy.
Creepy, creepy, creepy.

00:03:28.448 --> 00:03:33.108
Creepy.
What is this?

00:03:33.108 --> 00:03:35.728
I seriously have no idea.
There's no door.

00:03:38.748 --> 00:03:41.889
Whoa, wait.
What is this, seriously?

00:03:47.769 --> 00:03:50.749
Ah, it's cold.
So cold.

00:03:51.689 --> 00:03:56.469
I haven't even eaten anything.
Hey, hey, hey, be quiet.

00:03:56.469 --> 00:04:00.129
Don't yell, seriously.
What is this?

00:04:01.249 --> 00:04:03.869
What is this?
Whoa.

00:04:04.229 --> 00:04:07.830
I seriously can't handle this.
I only recognize Mitate. Mitate.

00:04:08.830 --> 00:04:14.650
Mitate. He's the only one I know. He's
wanted. I see.

00:04:17.090 --> 00:04:18.590
Ah.
So everybody's kind of...

00:04:18.750 --> 00:04:20.391
It means they're all captured.
Hmm.

00:04:20.701 --> 00:04:21.701
Huh.

00:04:22.171 --> 00:04:23.971
But the others, um...

00:04:24.371 --> 00:04:28.391
Everyone has things they need to clear in
their rooms,

00:04:29.011 --> 00:04:31.551
but what can Kuro-chan even do?
What's he supposed to do?

00:04:31.591 --> 00:04:34.272
Right?
He's just buried alive.

00:04:34.812 --> 00:04:41.792
The fact that he's cold in that
situation... That's the first time I've learned that.

00:04:41.832 --> 00:04:46.133
So if you're buried, it's cold.
Makes sense, the ground is chilly.

00:04:46.653 --> 00:04:49.733
Of course.
Oh, so it's cold.

00:04:50.013 --> 00:04:52.873
Underground,
the first thing you say is, 'It's cold.'

00:04:52.933 --> 00:04:55.933
Wow. I guess that's what makes it real.
That's interesting.

00:04:56.713 --> 00:05:00.594
But Kuro-chan being buried doesn't even
feel that weird. Yeah, exactly.

00:05:03.104 --> 00:05:04.104
Yeah.

00:05:12.875 --> 00:05:13.875
Uh...

00:05:21.945 --> 00:05:22.945
Here?

00:05:24.176 --> 00:05:26.236
What is this, a dump?
A dumping ground?

00:05:27.396 --> 00:05:31.416
Illegal dumping? Mountain dumping?
Huh? Was I dumped here?

00:05:33.236 --> 00:05:36.777
This is Wednesday, right?
It's the show, right?

00:05:37.937 --> 00:05:39.937
Then Kuro-chan ends up on Wednesday.
Wait a sec.

00:05:40.537 --> 00:05:43.917
Hey, aren't there way too few clues?
Is anyone there?

00:05:45.637 --> 00:05:48.678
I'm buried.
There's a person buried here.

00:05:49.158 --> 00:05:53.598
Is anyone actually here?
That's a real SOS.

00:05:53.618 --> 00:05:56.598
From what I can see. Is there something
behind me? I can't tell.

00:05:57.918 --> 00:06:01.679
It'd be terrifying if this were real.
Something like this probably happened somewhere.

00:06:01.679 --> 00:06:02.659
Yeah.
Yeah.

00:06:02.659 --> 00:06:06.599
What?
A speaker?

00:06:10.379 --> 00:06:13.740
What's this?
What's this?

00:06:14.740 --> 00:06:16.620
Huh?
Wait, what's this?

00:06:17.560 --> 00:06:19.600
A GoPro and
a letter.

00:06:19.700 --> 00:06:21.220
There was a letter.
A letter, a letter.

00:06:21.720 --> 00:06:23.620
It's cramped.
Huh?

00:06:23.640 --> 00:06:25.401
I see.
Huh?

00:06:25.741 --> 00:06:31.261
So that means I can eat it?

00:06:31.481 --> 00:06:34.681
Why are you so positive? Seriously.
It's all-you-can-eat candy.

00:06:34.961 --> 00:06:36.761
Is this real candy?
Don't get mad later.

00:06:36.901 --> 00:06:40.662
Hey.
Oh, I thought it was just a set.

00:06:41.682 --> 00:06:42.682
Whoa, amazing.

00:06:42.682 --> 00:06:43.762
This is gonna take a while,

00:06:49.262 --> 00:06:50.262
this.

00:06:50.473 --> 00:06:51.473
It's good.
Tasty?

00:06:52.543 --> 00:06:54.543
It's good.
What?

00:06:54.763 --> 00:06:59.783
Wait, wait.
That's way too vague.

00:07:00.323 --> 00:07:02.604
That's it?
Huh?

00:07:04.364 --> 00:07:07.244
So if it got picked,
that's what it means.

00:07:07.244 --> 00:07:11.004
So the radio name
has to be some Thai-sounding thing?

00:07:11.844 --> 00:07:12.984
For the escape...
Ah.

00:07:14.044 --> 00:07:16.685
...you work it into
your radio name, maybe.

00:07:16.705 --> 00:07:18.845
Anyway,
as long as we get out, right?

00:07:20.145 --> 00:07:22.905
I don't know how we're supposed to get
out. There isn't even an entrance.

00:07:23.265 --> 00:07:26.305
Wait, what?
How are we supposed to get out?

00:07:26.305 --> 00:07:27.766
Whoa.
And on top of that...

00:07:29.266 --> 00:07:32.218
No.
Ah, no good.

00:07:33.738 --> 00:07:36.558
Come on.
Wait, the entrance really...

00:07:36.998 --> 00:07:38.598
You're right, there's no door.
Hmm.

00:07:38.778 --> 00:07:40.078
Whoa, creepy.
This is scary.

00:07:40.078 --> 00:07:42.978
It says to get out.
No, r-right, that's the thing...

00:07:44.198 --> 00:07:47.319
Even if that's the rule,
are we supposed to smash it?

00:07:48.279 --> 00:07:51.479
No, that's the only option.
Are we allowed to burn it down?

00:07:52.099 --> 00:07:56.899
If we burn it, we'll die.
That's dangerous.

00:07:57.179 --> 00:08:00.419
If that radio name
were something like 'Lighter'...

00:08:01.199 --> 00:08:04.479
Ah, Lighter Hour.
If it were Lighter Hour, then a lighter...

00:08:04.479 --> 00:08:08.379
This is enough to drive you insane.
I might actually lose it.

00:08:08.379 --> 00:08:12.779
Hey.
Having no door is seriously stressful.

00:08:14.239 --> 00:08:18.140
Answer the quiz and escape this room.
Huh?

00:08:19.400 --> 00:08:22.860
No way, I'm bad at this stuff.
And why the hell is it Hosokawa Fumie?

00:08:24.189 --> 00:08:25.260
Well, telephone cards.
In their heyday.

00:08:25.260 --> 00:08:27.300
Seriously.
She really is pretty.

00:08:27.567 --> 00:08:28.853
That might be worth something.
That is so not the point.

00:08:30.020 --> 00:08:31.620
Wait a sec.
This is at least a little soothing.

00:08:31.740 --> 00:08:32.900
Hold on.
This...

00:08:34.140 --> 00:08:35.680
There are only 50 of them.
You're right.

00:08:37.140 --> 00:08:41.140
That's limited. Nobody keeps in touch by
phone number anymore.

00:08:41.230 --> 00:08:42.230
Exactly.
Young people...

00:08:42.350 --> 00:08:43.350
Wouldn't know.
Yeah.

00:08:44.180 --> 00:08:45.981
Me,
my parents' place and...

00:08:46.701 --> 00:08:48.801
I remember my wife's cell number.
Nice.

00:08:49.461 --> 00:08:51.601
As expected.
I don't remember anything.

00:08:51.701 --> 00:08:54.161
Wait, what would calling your parents do?
Think about whether it helps us escape.

00:08:54.361 --> 00:08:57.521
Oh, right, ask for a hint.
Six by four... 24. Twenty-four.

00:08:57.621 --> 00:09:02.301
There are 24 questions?
Damn, which ones can we answer?

00:09:02.301 --> 00:09:03.621
Ah, like this one.
Ah, this one.

00:09:04.341 --> 00:09:09.761
Move two matches and double it.
I think we can do this one.

00:09:10.481 --> 00:09:13.401
Ah, I know this one.
I know this one.

00:09:14.262 --> 00:09:18.302
Name the creature that kills the most
humans on Earth. That's a famous one.

00:09:19.442 --> 00:09:20.602
What is it?
Mosquito.

00:09:20.602 --> 00:09:25.222
Ah.
Right, right.

00:09:26.642 --> 00:09:28.822
Oh, c-can we press it?
We can.

00:09:28.822 --> 00:09:30.302
We can press it.
We can!

00:09:31.132 --> 00:09:32.132
Oh!
Whoa!

00:09:32.282 --> 00:09:34.442
Ah, wait.
Whoa!

00:09:34.442 --> 00:09:37.542
Whoa! What is this?
Keep pressing it.

00:09:37.582 --> 00:09:39.342
Go, go.
Hey! Hey!

00:09:40.202 --> 00:09:42.182
So that's if we answer right?
Where?

00:09:42.182 --> 00:09:44.963
Hey! Where?
So it spreads out like this?

00:09:45.003 --> 00:09:46.523
Huh.
Ah, I see.

00:09:46.963 --> 00:09:48.223
Wait, I got it.
What?

00:09:49.323 --> 00:09:51.903
And then we open it up
and get out?

00:09:52.183 --> 00:09:54.063
Ah, that's how it works.
Wait.

00:09:55.403 --> 00:09:56.563
So we can't do this.
It won't press.

00:09:56.563 --> 00:09:58.803
If we're wrong, we can't get through.
I see.

00:09:59.649 --> 00:10:00.863
Because we haven't answered right yet,
the far parts...

00:10:00.863 --> 00:10:02.303
...are useless.
We have to do it in order.

00:10:02.383 --> 00:10:05.063
So start with the nearby ones.
Clear the close ones first.

00:10:05.063 --> 00:10:07.943
With how skinny I am, maybe I could...
Wow, this is well made.

00:10:10.663 --> 00:10:11.924
Hmm.
Ah, I could get out from around here.

00:10:12.044 --> 00:10:15.684
Why only you?
Both of us have to get out.

00:10:17.824 --> 00:10:20.564
Hey, can you hear this over the speaker?
Me, from here...

00:10:20.684 --> 00:10:24.624
Hey, can you hear me talking?
You can, right?

00:10:25.144 --> 00:10:28.344
You can hear me, right?
I'm in trouble.

00:10:28.484 --> 00:10:32.364
Seriously, I'm in more trouble than you
think.

00:10:33.584 --> 00:10:38.524
I'm losing body heat and can't do
anything. Answer it!

00:10:39.304 --> 00:10:43.265
There must be staff somewhere, right?
Hey, somebody say something!

00:10:46.065 --> 00:10:50.485
Hey, is someone standing behind me?
Are you watching and laughing?

00:10:51.425 --> 00:10:55.925
Hey!
I can't turn around, so I can't tell.

00:10:58.925 --> 00:11:01.365
Huh?
Isn't this a speaker?

00:11:01.405 --> 00:11:03.525
No, it is a speaker.
Ah!

00:11:07.625 --> 00:11:10.946
Alexa?
It's Alexa!

00:11:10.946 --> 00:11:14.726
Alexa?
Alexa...

00:11:17.930 --> 00:11:20.830
Then that's not it!
Huh?

00:11:20.910 --> 00:11:23.151
Hey, Siri!
Ah, Siri!

00:11:26.751 --> 00:11:29.731
Isn't it Siri?
Hey, Siri!

00:11:30.652 --> 00:11:32.152
You need to project more.
I'm buried here.

00:11:32.832 --> 00:11:37.352
I'm buried here. Even if it responds, what
do I ask? Get me out of here?

00:11:37.532 --> 00:11:39.673
Was I buried?
Was there something?

00:11:40.773 --> 00:11:43.753
Wait, there is something, right? There is.
Ah.

00:11:43.833 --> 00:11:44.833
Um...
Um...

00:11:46.188 --> 00:11:47.759
Google, Google, um...
Um...

00:11:47.974 --> 00:11:50.914
It's Google.
Was there a phrase? Uh, hey...

00:11:52.500 --> 00:11:54.214
Hey, Google!
Isn't it 'OK, Google'?

00:11:54.214 --> 00:11:56.575
OK, Google?
Oh!

00:11:56.915 --> 00:11:59.455
Ah, something lit up.
Yes, how can I help you?

00:11:59.455 --> 00:12:02.935
Huh.
Huh? It said something, it said something.

00:12:02.935 --> 00:12:03.935
Huh?
OK, Google!

00:12:05.036 --> 00:12:10.816
Ah, it lit up, it lit up.
Hello. How are you today?

00:12:11.996 --> 00:12:13.637
Not good.
Not good.

00:12:13.817 --> 00:12:19.317
That's worrying. Are you getting enough
sleep? No, I can't sleep. If I do, I'm dead.

00:12:20.317 --> 00:12:22.998
And I'm freezing.
Don't keep saying that.

00:12:23.158 --> 00:12:26.538
It must be seriously cold
if he's wedged in that much.

00:12:26.978 --> 00:12:33.219
Are you sleeping well? Answer yes or no.
Yes, ah, just say yes.

00:12:34.939 --> 00:12:36.919
I didn't quite catch that.
Why not?

00:12:38.260 --> 00:12:41.340
I said it.
No, wait, this isn't the time for that...

00:12:42.360 --> 00:12:44.740
This is probably the hint.
It's a hint, got it.

00:12:45.581 --> 00:12:51.481
If we talk to this, it'll give us the
answer, right? What kind of burp was that?

00:12:51.481 --> 00:12:52.552
What should I ask?
OK, Google!

00:12:56.122 --> 00:12:57.742
Where is this?
Ah.

00:12:58.342 --> 00:13:00.582
Location information isn't registered.
Ah.

00:13:01.602 --> 00:13:04.203
Useless!
So it doesn't even know where this is.

00:13:05.043 --> 00:13:08.443
At this point, I just have to keep eating.
It's about what you eat to get out.

00:13:08.443 --> 00:13:13.044
Yeah, I guess so.
There are salty snacks too.

00:13:13.044 --> 00:13:15.404
Potato chips.
Rice crackers.

00:13:15.404 --> 00:13:20.305
Wow, they really went all out.
Chocolate, marshmallows.

00:13:22.605 --> 00:13:26.625
Um, and what's this? Baumkuchen?
It is baumkuchen.

00:13:26.665 --> 00:13:28.726
Wow, that's the easiest one to eat.
Marshmallows.

00:13:29.886 --> 00:13:31.046
Marshmallows?
Marshmallows.

00:13:32.209 --> 00:13:34.066
Huh? I can't eat that many marshmallows.
Marshmallows sound good.

00:13:34.066 --> 00:13:38.227
Marshmallows.
Wow, this is like a dream.

00:13:39.447 --> 00:13:41.247
Yeah.
Amazing.

00:13:41.247 --> 00:13:43.267
Wow.
Ah, it's good.

00:13:43.267 --> 00:13:47.328
Tasty.
You look happy.

00:13:47.848 --> 00:13:52.309
True, I like marshmallows too.
I still wish we could press something.

00:13:52.309 --> 00:13:55.489
It's amazing.
Tasty, though.

00:13:55.569 --> 00:13:59.589
It's good, but...
Sweet.

00:14:00.309 --> 00:14:04.370
You get sick of sweet stuff.
I can see wafers in the back.

00:14:04.730 --> 00:14:09.131
Yeah.
Ah.

00:14:09.491 --> 00:14:11.771
There is some light back there, kind of.

00:14:13.731 --> 00:14:18.112
Like a tiny gap you see between plywood
boards. Hmm.

00:14:18.132 --> 00:14:19.252
There is.
Like that.

00:14:19.352 --> 00:14:25.913
Wafers.
This feels like a prison.

00:14:25.993 --> 00:14:31.053
It's good, though.
Ah, this part lifts a little.

00:14:31.053 --> 00:14:32.053
It lifts.
Yeah.

00:14:34.350 --> 00:14:36.730
It's barely going down.
This is rough too.

00:14:36.810 --> 00:14:38.070
Was it always this fast?
You're in the way.

00:14:38.871 --> 00:14:40.751
Was it always this fast?
This makes absolutely no sense.

00:14:40.751 --> 00:14:42.591
Yeah.
Like...

00:14:43.351 --> 00:14:44.851
Well, yeah.
A chainsaw, maybe.

00:14:45.331 --> 00:14:46.852
A chainsaw.
A saw.

00:14:46.912 --> 00:14:49.192
We may have to destroy it.
A hammer.

00:14:50.292 --> 00:14:52.892
A hammer, huh.
Wait, are we allowed to break it?

00:14:53.432 --> 00:14:56.953
Can we brute-force this?
Shouldn't this be more about brains?

00:14:58.133 --> 00:15:01.533
Seriously, what even is this material?
It doesn't feel like something to smash.

00:15:01.533 --> 00:15:03.614
I seriously don't get this.
It feels like outer space in here.

00:15:04.294 --> 00:15:09.034
The light is nothing but white. If you
stayed here for days, you'd go insane.

00:15:09.054 --> 00:15:11.475
This really...
I've seen movies like this.

00:15:11.595 --> 00:15:16.415
Yeah, it feels like a movie set.
A building, or whatever.

00:15:17.075 --> 00:15:21.996
Why is everything white?
They want to drive us crazy. Has to be.

00:15:22.436 --> 00:15:24.756
It's like one of those experiments
you're never supposed to do.

00:15:26.077 --> 00:15:29.737
Still, all I can think of is a hammer.
What else? A c-chainsaw.

00:15:30.597 --> 00:15:31.917
Have you ever used a chainsaw?
No.

00:15:32.697 --> 00:15:37.138
No. Then you haven't used one, right?
You've never used one?

00:15:37.818 --> 00:15:41.599
Actually, a long time ago, I once did
civil work... You did?

00:15:41.759 --> 00:15:46.819
When I was a temp worker, they let me hold
one for a second. I didn't use it, but it was scary.

00:15:47.219 --> 00:15:49.520
Yeah.
It doesn't go 'whirr' like you'd think.

00:15:49.520 --> 00:15:51.960
Yeah.
It jerks like bam.

00:15:52.020 --> 00:15:54.320
It's scary.
Feels like it'd kick back.

00:15:54.400 --> 00:15:58.341
Seriously. You hold it like this, and this
happens. Oh.

00:15:59.201 --> 00:16:03.201
Like Chainsaw Man,
but in reverse.

00:16:03.201 --> 00:16:06.042
Seriously.
That kickback is what makes them scary.

00:16:06.382 --> 00:16:11.642
What if we peel off just one piece? Right,
first we need something to scratch it with.

00:16:12.902 --> 00:16:14.563
Or a pickaxe.
A pickaxe, yeah.

00:16:14.843 --> 00:16:17.763
In the end, a pickaxe might be best.
Yeah.

00:16:18.023 --> 00:16:20.423
